I had an idea before going to sleep. Hope you guys like it.

A ship, lost in the depths of space, awaiting rescue of some sort. No one had missed them, it looked, and a couple of thousands of years had passed before I found them, rather ironically since I got lost too.

Stumbling into their ship was no easy task, no. Ships that old tended to have hidden traps, and I didn't want to risk it. But my small ship wasn't suited to travel between galaxies and until the Repair Service came there would be need to wait there 8 to 10 hours.

In the end, I decided to dock there. As long as I remained in the bridge and didn't look inside, I was going to be fine, I told myself. Oh boy, if I only knew.

Docking and taking the elevator to the bridge was easy. Electricity and running water were still functioning, rather surprisingly, and to entertain myself I had my smartphone to some episodes of a series I recently started to watch.

I took a seat in what looked like the captain's seat. Big mistake.

As soon as I did it, some kind of alarm started to whine loudly through the speakers, leaving me almost deaf. Panicking, I tried to go back to the ship's bay, but the doors were locked!

Before I could think about it, I felt a big impact on my head. Laying in the floor, seconds before passing out, the only thing I could see was robotic legs. Robotics legs! And everything went dark.

PS: I'm the new guy from two threads ago. Yeah, the one talking about how 4chan doesn't have an account system. Oliver_Hart, you may remind me. Gotta keep writing!
